sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Retrieves the headers of a sheet.

Note: Flow designers must ensure that this action is always used in conjunction with actions that use sheet headers as dynamic inputs.

Inputs:

  • Connection & Credential Alias: Connection & credential alias of Google Sheets Spoke.
  • Spreadsheet ID: Unique identifier of spreadsheet which can be extracted from a Google Sheets URL - https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/spreadsheetId
  • Sheet: Title of the sheet.

Outputs:

  • Sheets: JSON containing headers of the specified sheet. The sheet headers from Google Sheets response body have been mapped to label and name fields in JSON output.
    Example of JSON output: 
    {
"data":[
{
"label":"Header1",
"name":"Header1",
"value":""
},
{
"label":"Header2",
"name":"Header2",
"value":""
}
]
}
  • Status: If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Sheets, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message: Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Sheet or Range.
  • Spreadsheet not found for given ID.
  • Enable Google Sheets API for the project in the app console.
  • Invalid access token.
  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Sheets connection and credential must be created and associated with the GoogleSheets Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note : Requires a subscription for production use. Read More

sys_hub_action_type_snapshot.description:
Retrieves the headers of a sheet.

Note: Flow designers must ensure that this action is always used in conjunction with actions that use sheet headers as dynamic inputs.

Inputs:

  • Connection & Credential Alias: Connection & credential alias of Google Sheets Spoke.
  • Spreadsheet ID: Unique identifier of spreadsheet which can be extracted from a Google Sheets URL - https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/spreadsheetId
  • Sheet: Title of the sheet.

Outputs:

  • Sheets: JSON containing headers of the specified sheet. The sheet headers from Google Sheets response body have been mapped to label and name fields in JSON output.
    Example of JSON output: 
    {
"data":[
{
"label":"Header1",
"name":"Header1",
"value":""
},
{
"label":"Header2",
"name":"Header2",
"value":""
}
]
}
  • Status: If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Sheets, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message: Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Sheet or Range.
  • Spreadsheet not found for given ID.
  • Enable Google Sheets API for the project in the app console.
  • Invalid access token.
  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Sheets connection and credential must be created and associated with the GoogleSheets Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note : Requires a subscription for production use. Read More
